I think I got this game when I first got my iPhone. Probably played it once or twice but then lost interest. Maybe I was distracted by all the glitz and 3d-ness of the latest games. I don't know why I thought of playing it tonight, but wife and I are here lying in bed and were both needing off with our iPhones and I opened that app. Played a few levels and I was hooked.  So few games carry with them the multiple dimensions of play from across so many genres. For example, the game has great action and decent graphics. It also utilizes ones logic, with time enough to think about each move. It requires a certain dexterity to properly time the release of each type of explosive device in your arsenal. Yes I can see I'm going to like this app. Wonder when I'll care to play Angry Birds again.
